### Q2.  List Files in Unix   

What do the following commands do:  
`ls`  
`ls -a`  
`ls -l`  
`ls -lh`  
`ls -lah`  
`ls -t`  
`ls -Glp`  

> > ls :lists all files in directory
ls -a :includes all entries; appears to list them all alphabetically
ls -l : displays long format listing 
ls -lh :long format with file size
ls -lah : includes all entries in readable, long format   
---

### Q3.  More List Files in Unix  

Explore these other [ls options](http://www.techonthenet.com/unix/basic/ls.php) and pick 5 of your favorites:

> > ls -p :displays directories with /
ls -t : displays newest files (based on timestamp)
ls -r : displays in reverse order
ls -R : displays subdirectories
ls -d : displys only diectories 
