### Q4.  Xargs   

What does `xargs` do? Give an example of how to use it.

> > allows you to build and execute commans and apply given command to series of items, in order

e.g., code below allows you to delete all files with 2014 in its name,  rather than doing it 
find . -name "*2014*" | xargs rm -rf

 

